# LucidGate example list: exceptionregexpurllist
# Format: One Go regular expression per line. It is matched against the canonical URL including scheme, host, path and query.
# Lines beginning with # are comments and are ignored by the loader.
# To activate a rule, copy one example, remove the leading # and adapt it to your environment.
# You can include another file with: .Include<relative-or-absolute-path>
#
# Commented examples:
# ^https://example\.test/private($|/|\?)
# ^https://[^/]+\.example\.test/admin($|/|\?)
# /download/.*\.(exe|dll)$
# [?&]debug=true(&|$)
# ^http://legacy\.example\.test/
# /api/(export|dump)($|/|\?)
# /token=[A-Za-z0-9_-]+
# ^https://files\.example\.test/secrets/
# /redirect\?to=http%3A%2F%2F
# ^https://repo\.example\.test/internal/
